 the automatic garage door opener.";i:1;s:43:"Why Did My Garage Door Remote Stop Working.";i:2;s:78:"These are the most common reasons why your garage door remote stopped working.";i:3;s:48:"The first and simplest reason is a dead battery.";i:4;s:154:"Nothing is more frustrating then pulling into your driveway and clicking your remote only to find the signal is not being transmitted to your garage door.";i:5;s:51:"Your garage door is not responding and we can help.";i:6;s:74:"The most common problem is that the battery inside of your remote is dead.";i:7;s:127:"So youre arriving home pulling into your driveway and hitting the button on your garage door opener remote and nothing happens.";i:8;s:126:"The Garage Door Remote Wont Work but the Wall Switch Does Check the batteries and clean the electrical contacts in the remote.";i:9;s:58:"If the remote does not work try re-programming the remote.";i:10;s:41:"Garage Door Remote Not Working - YouTube.";i:11;s:71:"If it is within range but still does not work there are ways to fix it.";i:12;s:107:"Check the Batteries The most common cause of garage door remote control failure are weak or dead batteries.";i:13;s:113:"If youre still having trouble programming your garage door opener dont hesitate to contact us for a service call.";i:14;s:140:"If youre not in the Central Jersey area please call Overhead Door Corporation at 800-929-3667 for the Overhead Door distributor nearest you.";i:15;s:40:"Remote Openers Programming Instructions.";i:16;s:63:"How to fix a Garage Door Opener - Remote not working - YouTube.";i:17;s:193:"Although these troubleshooting tips are shown for a Craftsman garage door opener with remotes not working the repair advice also works for common Chamberlain and Liftmaster garage door openers.";i:18;s:112:"Check out more troubleshooting tips articles videos and repair guides on our DIY garage door opener repair page.";i:19;s:114:"Troubleshooting tips for when your garage door remote suddenly stops working andor the buttons are not responding.";i:20;s:63:"The most common cause for remote not working is dead batteries.";i:21;s:29:"So check the batteries first.";i:22;s:54:"Access the batteries by opening the panel on the back.";i:23;s:57:"If your device has screws remove them and open the panel.";i:24;s:61:"Press and hold the button until the led light by it goes out.";i:25;s:60:"This erases all codes from the machine so more can be input.";i:26;s:127:"With remotes in hand press the learn button like a door bell and then the button on the remote and the light bulb should flash.";i:27;s:49:"This tells you that the remote has been accepted.";i:28;s:29:"Repeat for all other remotes.";i:29;s:131:"A remote control uses batteries to send wireless signals so a dead battery may cause it to fail even though the door control works.";i:30;s:209:"Your garage door opener is equipped with an integrated receiver logic board that receives a signal from for your hand-held remote controls wirelessly whereas your wall-mounted door control panel is hard-wired.";i:31;s:105:"Some of the reasons why an overhead door remote might be malfunctioning or unresponsive are stated below.";i:32;s:44:"The remote controls batteries might be dead.";i:33;s:128:"The possibility that the batteries may be weak or dead is the most common reason why overhead door remote controls stop working.";i:34;s:66:"It is best to replace the batteries with their exact replacements.";i:35;s:131:"There once was a time when a garage door opener was a teenager running through the rain to open the door for the family luxury van.";i:36;s:50:"These days we tend to take the remote for granted.";i:37;s:105:"But when the garage door opener remote stops working it can seem like the entire worlds ground to a halt.";i:38;s:65:"Garage Door Remote Is Not Working Consistently Drained Batteries.";i:39;s:79:"The most common reason for an unresponsive garage door remote is the batteries.";i:40;s:16:"Lock Mode is On.";i:41;s:60:"Another easy fix that we often overlook is the lock mode on.";i:42;s:227:"You also must have access to the inside of your garage to perform this garage door keypad repair it wont work if youre locked out If your keypad is closing your garage but not opening it have your partner stand near the keypad.";i:43;s:105:"Set the ladder up near your garage door motor and carefully climb up to the point where you can reach it.";i:44;s:80:"After pressing the learn button on the side of the motor your partner will have.";}}